SUMMARY:Day 2: Orientation Day 1
DESCRIPTION:\nNote: \n\nWhen you arrive on campus\, follow the signs for Orientation and park in the Lot 22 Parking Structure. All vehicles on campus must have a valid campus parking permit. You will enter your vehicle's license plate information to purchase an ePermit from a kiosk in the parking lot. **Parking permits cost $8 per day. You will have the option to select an Orientation parking permit to be valid for the entire Orientation program for $16.** \n\nFor directions to UCSB\, see https://www.ucsb.edu/about/visit\n\n[Parent & Family Schedule](https://orientation.sa.ucsb.edu/parent/freshman-parent-family-orientation-information#parents-program-schedule)\n[Freshman Orientation Program Information](https://orientation.sa.ucsb.edu/freshman/program-information) 
URL:https://troyh.github.io/TravelItinerary/?i=it-a44dcfe4&day=2
UID:day-2-20260713@travelitinerary
END:VEVENT
